        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 5:57PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 557 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Madison, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Huntsville, Decatur, Madison, Athens, Moores Mill, Redstone Arsenal,
Meridianville, Hazel Green, Priceville, and Gurley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
